response.overview: NJPW Wrestling World 1999 took place on January 4, 1999, at the Tokyo Dome in Tokyo, Japan. This professional wrestling spectacle features Keiji Muto challenging Scott Norton for the IWGP Heavyweight Championship in the main event. Other key matchups include Shinya Hashimoto vs. Naoya Ogawa in a New Japan vs. UFO clash, Genichiro Tenryu & Shiro Koshinaka defending the IWGP Tag Team titles against Hiroyoshi Tenzan & Satoshi Kojima, and Jushin Liger facing Koji Kanemoto for the IWGP Junior Heavyweight Championship. Additional bouts showcase Manabu Nakanishi vs. Kazuyuki Fujita and a six-man tag with Tatsumi Fujinami, Osamu Kido, and Tadao Yasuda against Heisei Ishingun. It’s the eighth annual January 4 Tokyo Dome Show, drawing 52,500 fans for NJPW’s biggest night of the year.
response.title: NJPW Wrestling World 1999
